			<IMG align="left" style="margin-right:20px;margin-bottom:20px;" src="/assets/home-exercises.jpg" /><P align="justify">There's a wide variety of home exercises that you can perform with no equipment - all you need is a bit of knowledge and some motivation or maybe consider a <A href="//www.onelifestyle.co.uk">personal trainer?</A><BR />&nbsp;<BR />If you add just a step box and some hand weights, then the range of home exercises you can perform will increase dramatically.<BR /><BR />Indeed, if you check through the other areas of the site you will find that many regular exercises can be adapted for home use. it's not about a <A target="_blank" class="txt" href="http://www.toning-belt.co.uk">toning belt</A> or other quick fixes - you need to get stuck in.<BR /><BR /><SPAN class="txtadfloat"><script type="text/javascript"><!--
